Describes a list of Batch jobs

Source: R/batch_operations.R
batch_describe_jobs.Rd

Describes a list of Batch jobs.

batch_describe_jobs(jobs)

Arguments

jobs

[required] A list of up to 100 job IDs.

Value

A list with the following syntax:

list(

    list(
      jobArn = "string",
      jobName = "string",
      jobId = "string",

      shareIdentifier = "string",

        list(

            networkInterfaces = list(
              list(
                attachmentId = "string",

                privateIpv4Address = "string"

          ),
          startedAt = 123,
          stoppedAt = 123,
          statusReason = "string"
        )
      ),
      statusReason = "string",
      createdAt = 123,
      retryStrategy = list(
        attempts = 123,

          list(

        list(
          jobId = "string",

        "string"
      ),

        image = "string",

        memory = 123,

          "string"

Request syntax

svc$describe_jobs(
  jobs = list(
    "string"
  )
)

Examples

if (FALSE) {
# This example describes a job with the specified job ID.
svc$describe_jobs(
  jobs = list(
    "24fa2d7a-64c4-49d2-8b47-f8da4fbde8e9"
  )
)
}
